title: Brunei Food Inflation
description: Cost of food in Brunei increased 7 percent in August of 2022 over the same month in the previous year. Food Inflation in Brunei averaged 1.47 percent from 2007 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 8.34 percent in April of 2012 and a record low of -2.41 percent in February of 2010. This page provides the latest reported value for - Brunei Food Inflation - plus previous releases, historical high and low, short-term forecast and long-term prediction, economic calendar, survey consensus and news.
author: Department of Economic Planning and Development, Brunei
